## Vercel Speed Insights Implementation

Successfully installed and configured Vercel Speed Insights for this React + Vite project.

### Changes Made

**Modified Files:**

1. **package.json**
   - Added `@vercel/speed-insights` version `^2.0.0` as a dependency

2. **package-lock.json**
   - Updated with the new package and its dependencies (203 new packages)

3. **src/App.tsx**
   - Added import: `import { SpeedInsights } from '@vercel/speed-insights/react';`
   - Added `<SpeedInsights />` component alongside the existing `<VercelAnalytics />` component in the Router context

### Implementation Details

- Fetched the latest installation instructions from official Vercel documentation
- Identified this as a React + Vite project (not Next.js)
- Used the React-specific package (`@vercel/speed-insights/react`) as per the documentation
- Placed the SpeedInsights component at the app root level in App.tsx, alongside the existing Analytics component
- This ensures Speed Insights will track performance metrics across all pages

### Verification

- ✅ Build completed successfully with no errors
- ✅ Linter passed for App.tsx (no new errors introduced)
- ✅ Lock file properly updated with new dependencies

### Notes

The project already had `@vercel/analytics` installed, so the Speed Insights integration follows the same pattern for consistency. The SpeedInsights component will automatically start collecting performance metrics once deployed to Vercel.

To view Speed Insights data:
1. Deploy the application to Vercel
2. Enable Speed Insights in the Vercel dashboard under your project settings
3. Access metrics through the Speed Insights tab in the dashboard after user visits
